Python is a powerful and easy to learn language. 
It has efficient high level data structure and effective apporach to OOP. It has dynamic typing, elegant syntax together with its interpreted nature.


Python is completely free to download and use, and you can share it with anyone — no license fees involved. It also comes packed with built-in tools for common tasks, plus you can find tons of extra free add-ons on python.org made by other developers.
If you need extra speed, programmers can write parts of Python in C or C++ and plug them in like a turbocharger. 
And other software (like Blender or GIMP) can embed Python inside itself, so users can customize that software using simple Python scripts instead of complex code.

Python can either take commands one-by-one live (interactive mode, good for testing small things) or run a whole saved file at once (script mode, good for real programs) 
and by default it assumes your code files use UTF-8 so you can freely use text from any language.
